cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new method for noise level estimation, which involves statistical techniques and information theory, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely sub-categories as well. The proposed method also involves machine learning techniques, such as Wiener filtering, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
